plCdNumber.name: plCdNumber
plCdNumber.description: Number of Cards available. Maximum index of plCdTable

plCdTable.name: plCdTable
plCdTable.description: Powerline Cards Table. List of attributes of each Card available in the System. Indexed by the number of the Card (from 1 to plCdNumber).

plCdIndex.name: plCdIndex
plCdIndex.description: Number of powerline card. Maximum: plCdNumber

plCdLink.name: plCdLink
plCdLink.description: Type of link: 1 => Link 1 2 => Link 2 3 => Link 3 4 => Link 4 5 => Link 5 6 => Link 6

plCdShortMacAddress.name: plCdShortMacAddress
plCdShortMacAddress.description: Short MAC Address of the Card

plCdLongMacAddress.name: plCdLongMacAddress
plCdLongMacAddress.description: Long MAC Address of the Card

plCdReset.name: plCdReset
plCdReset.description: Reset to Saved Values. Soft Reset.

plCdFactoryReset.name: plCdFactoryReset
plCdFactoryReset.description: Reset to factory values. Hard Reset.

plCdSaveAsPermanent.name: plCdSaveAsPermanent
plCdSaveAsPermanent.description: Save MIB values as default values: the information of the Remote List (long MAC address and short MAC address of each user) is saved and will be restored after a reboot or a poweroff.

plCdStatus.name: plCdStatus
plCdStatus.description: Status related to the interface: 0 => OK.

plCdRemoteList.name: plCdRemoteList
plCdRemoteList.description: List of Long MAC Address that can be connected with HE (only HE). Returns a string with the list of long MAC address (not separated by spaces)

plCdNumRemoteList.name: plCdNumRemoteList
plCdNumRemoteList.description: Number of CPE in remote list (only HE). This is the maximum value for cpeId in Network table.

plNetTable.name: plNetTable
plNetTable.description: Network Topology. Indexed by number of card and number of remote user (.plCdIndex.cpeId). Maximum values for indexes: plCdNumber and plCdNumRemoteList. Only available in HE.

plNetLongMacAddress.name: plNetLongMacAddress
plNetLongMacAddress.description: Long Mac Address of Remote Node.

plInpTable.name: plInpTable
plInpTable.description: Input Channel Table. Common input characteristics. Indexed by number of card. Maximum value of index: plCdNumber

plInpTotalOctets.name: plInpTotalOctets
plInpTotalOctets.description: Total number of rx octets (including FEC overhead)

plInpAGC.name: plInpAGC
plInpAGC.description: To enable or disable Adaptive Rx Gain Control. 0 => AGC disabled 1 => AGC enabled.

plInpThresholds.name: plInpThresholds
plInpThresholds.description: SNR Thresholds in dB. Returns a string containing 4 integers.

plInpNodeReceivedPkts.name: plInpNodeReceivedPkts
plInpNodeReceivedPkts.description: Number of Packets received from cpeId user

plInpNodeReceivedCorrectedPkts.name: plInpNodeReceivedCorrectedPkts
plInpNodeReceivedCorrectedPkts.description: Number of Corrected (by FEC) received packets

plInpNodeReceivedCorrectedOctets.name: plInpNodeReceivedCorrectedOctets
plInpNodeReceivedCorrectedOctets.description: Number of Corrected (by FEC) received bytes

plInpNodeMeanBPC.name: plInpNodeMeanBPC
plInpNodeMeanBPC.description: Mean BPC: sum of current bits configuration

plInpNodeSNR.name: plInpNodeSNR
plInpNodeSNR.description: String with SNR per carrier: contains 512 bytes if it is a HE or 768 if it is a CPE.

plInpNodeBPC.name: plInpNodeBPC
plInpNodeBPC.description: String with BPC per carrier configuration: contains 256 bytes if it is a HE or 384 if it is a CPE.

plInpNodeCFR.name: plInpNodeCFR
plInpNodeCFR.description: String with CFR per carrier: contains 512 bytes if it is a HE or 768 if it is a CPE.

plInpNodeEnableCarriers.name: plInpNodeEnableCarriers
plInpNodeEnableCarriers.description: String with enabled (1) and disabled (0) carriers: contains 256 bytes if it is a HE or 384 if it is a CPE.

plInpNodeProtocolEnableCarriers.name: plInpNodeProtocolEnableCarriers
plInpNodeProtocolEnableCarriers.description: String with enabled (1) and disabled (0) carriers: contains 256 bytes if it is a HE or 384 if it is a CPE.

serialNumber.name: serialNumber
serialNumber.description: The serial number of the board, which is unique per part number

partNumber.name: partNumber
partNumber.description: The part number of the board, which identifies the board type

rombootVersion.name: rombootVersion
rombootVersion.description: The string that identifies the Romboot software

alarms.name: alarms
alarms.description: Dynamic alarm table - shows all the outstanding alarms on the system

alarmIndex.name: alarmIndex
alarmIndex.description: The alarmIndex uniquely identifies alarms on the system

linuxVersion.name: linuxVersion
linuxVersion.description: The string that identifies the Linux kernel software

amperionSysDescr.name: amperionSysDescr
amperionSysDescr.description: A textual description of the entity. This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software. It is mandatory that this only contain printable ASCII characters.

amperionSysObjectID.name: amperionSysObjectID
amperionSysObjectID.description: The vendor's authoritative identification of the network management subsystem contained in the entity. This value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1) and provides an easy and unambiguous means for determining `what kind of box' is being managed. For example, if vendor `Flintstones, Inc.' was assigned the subtree 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242, it could assign the identifier 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242.1.1 to its `Fred Router'.

amperionSysUpTime.name: amperionSysUpTime
amperionSysUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

amperionSysContact.name: amperionSysContact
amperionSysContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.

amperionSysName.name: amperionSysName
amperionSysName.description: An administratively-assigned name for this managed node. By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name.

amperionSysLocation.name: amperionSysLocation
amperionSysLocation.description: The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor').

amperionSysServices.name: amperionSysServices
amperionSysServices.description: A value which indicates the set of services that this entity primarily offers. The value is a sum. This sum initially takes the value zero, Then, for each layer, L, in the range 1 through 7, that this node performs transactions for, 2 raised to (L - 1) is added to the sum. For example, a node which performs primarily routing functions would have a value of 4 (2^(3-1)). In contrast, a node which is a host offering application services would have a value of 72 (2^(4-1) + 2^(7-1)). Note that in the context of the Internet suite of protocols, values should be calculated accordingly: layer functionality 1 physical (e.g., repeaters) 2 datalink/subnetwork (e.g., bridges) 3 internet (e.g., IP gateways) 4 end-to-end (e.g., IP hosts) 7 applications (e.g., mail relays) For systems including OSI protocols, layers 5 and 6 may also be counted.

amperionTrapMgr1.name: amperionTrapMgr1
amperionTrapMgr1.description: IP address of Manager receceiving traps

amperionTrapMgr2.name: amperionTrapMgr2
amperionTrapMgr2.description: IP address of Manager receceiving traps

userGpsInfoString.name: userGpsInfoString
userGpsInfoString.description: User defined string for the user to put the GPS info of this device

serverAddress.name: serverAddress
serverAddress.description: Name or IP Address of the primary file server from which to retrieve new software.

currentState.name: currentState
currentState.description: Current state of the software upgrade.

bootPartition.name: bootPartition
bootPartition.description: Image in this partition will be used when the system boots.

upgradePartition.name: upgradePartition
upgradePartition.description: Default partition to erase and load with a new image.

currentPartition.name: currentPartition
currentPartition.description: Partition from which currently running software was loaded.

commandOptions.name: commandOptions
commandOptions.description: Software upgrade options: Reserved for future use

primaryPartitionContents.name: primaryPartitionContents
primaryPartitionContents.description: Description of image in primary partition.

primaryCRC.name: primaryCRC
primaryCRC.description: CRC status of image in primary partition.

backupPartitionContents.name: backupPartitionContents
backupPartitionContents.description: Description of image in backup partition.

backupCRC.name: backupCRC
backupCRC.description: CRC status of image in backup partition.

lastStatus.name: lastStatus
lastStatus.description: Status of current or last software upgrade performed (since last reboot).

filename.name: filename
filename.description: Path to filename to retrieve for software upgrade

server1Address.name: server1Address
server1Address.description: Name or IP Address of the alternate file server from which to retrieve new software.

server2Address.name: server2Address
server2Address.description: Name or IP Address of the second alternate file server from which to retrieve new software.

upgradeSchedule.name: upgradeSchedule
upgradeSchedule.description: Scheduled upgrade date and time in MMDDhhmm format.

rebootSchedule.name: rebootSchedule
rebootSchedule.description: Scheduled reboot date and time in MMDDhhmm format.

login.name: login
login.description: login to use for software upgrade file server access.

password.name: password
password.description: password to use for software upgrade file server access.

psImageChecksumError.name: psImageChecksumError
psImageChecksumError.description: The power supply is notifying the main digital board that its main image crc is incorrect. The main digital board needs to reprogram the new power supply image again, or revert back to an older good image

criticalBatteryShutdownWarning.name: criticalBatteryShutdownWarning
criticalBatteryShutdownWarning.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that we have lost AC Line voltage and the battery is running low. The system will be shutting down in seconds. Perform necessary backup.

p12vOutOfRange.name: p12vOutOfRange
p12vOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the +12v regulator is out of range. If the condition is such that it is too high, the decision may be to shutdown the regulator to avoid destroying the hardware

m8point5vOutOfRange.name: m8point5vOutOfRange
m8point5vOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the -8.5v regulator is out of range. Note that the -8.5v regulator is the same regulator as the +12v. If the condition is such that it is too high, the decision may be to shutdown the regulator to avoid destroying the hardware.

p5vOutOfRange.name: p5vOutOfRange
p5vOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the +5v regulator is out of range. If the condition is such that it is too high, the decision may be to shutdown the regulator to avoid destroying the hardware.

p3point3vOutOfRange.name: p3point3vOutOfRange
p3point3vOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the +3.3v regulator is out of range. If the condition is such that it is too high, the decision may be to shutdown the regulator to avoid destroying the hardware.

batteryVoltsOutOfRange.name: batteryVoltsOutOfRange
batteryVoltsOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the battery voltage is out of range.

mcuTempOutOfRange.name: mcuTempOutOfRange
mcuTempOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the microcontroller unit core temperature is out of range.

batteryTempOutOfRange.name: batteryTempOutOfRange
batteryTempOutOfRange.description: The power supply is warning the main digital board that the battery temperature is out of range

psDetectedCommLapse.name: psDetectedCommLapse
psDetectedCommLapse.description: Power Supply notifies main digital board that it did not communnicate to the power supply within the agreed upon periodic interval

criticalRequestAborted.name: criticalRequestAborted
criticalRequestAborted.description: The power supply is notifying the main digital board that one of the critical requests was aborted due to not receiving it twice in a row.

powerSupplyInternalError.name: powerSupplyInternalError
powerSupplyInternalError.description: Power Supply / netmgt (PS thread) detected an internal error condition

psBatteryNotConnected.name: psBatteryNotConnected
psBatteryNotConnected.description: Power Supply Battery Not Connected. There is no battery backup for the system.

psAcOnOff.name: psAcOnOff
psAcOnOff.description: Power Supply detected AC going ON / OFF

psHardwareError.name: psHardwareError
psHardwareError.description: The power supply is notifying the main digital board that it incurred a hardware error

npuDetectedCommLapse.name: npuDetectedCommLapse
npuDetectedCommLapse.description: Network processing unit could not communnicate to the power supply

powerCycleNpu.name: powerCycleNpu
powerCycleNpu.description: Power Cycle the Network Processor Unit

psMode.name: psMode
psMode.description: Power Supply mode, normal mode is protocol; dump mode is a debug mode which displays debug prints from the MCU

shutdownNpu.name: shutdownNpu
shutdownNpu.description: Shut down 12v, -8.5v, 3.3v and 5v regulators driving the Network Processor Unit. This should only be used if one of the voltages is too high.

psEt.name: psEt
psEt.description: Power Supply elapsed time since powerup

npuEt.name: npuEt
npuEt.description: Power Supply elapsed time since powerup

npuPuTimes.name: npuPuTimes
npuPuTimes.description: Number of times the Network Processing Unit has been powered up.

eventDescription.name: eventDescription
eventDescription.description: Description of the Last Event - Used in sending traps

psHardwareVersion.name: psHardwareVersion
psHardwareVersion.description: Hardware Version of the Power SUpply

interfaceAdminDown.name: interfaceAdminDown
interfaceAdminDown.description: Admin of Interface being set down

amperionifNumber.name: amperionifNumber
amperionifNumber.description: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

amperionifTable.name: amperionifTable
amperionifTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber.

amperionifDescr.name: amperionifDescr
amperionifDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

amperionifType.name: amperionifType
amperionifType.description: The type of interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack.

amperionifMtu.name: amperionifMtu
amperionifMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

amperionifSpeed.name: amperionifSpeed
amperionifSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth.

amperionifPhysAddress.name: amperionifPhysAddress
amperionifPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

amperionifAdminStatus.name: amperionifAdminStatus
amperionifAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

amperionifOperStatus.name: amperionifOperStatus
amperionifOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the interface. The testing(3) state indicates that no operational packets can be passed.

amperionifLastChange.name: amperionifLastChange
amperionifLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time the interface entered its current operational state. If the current state was entered prior to the last re- initialization of the local network management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

amperionifInOctets.name: amperionifInOctets
amperionifInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

amperionifInUcastPkts.name: amperionifInUcastPkts
amperionifInUcastPkts.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

amperionifInNUcastPkts.name: amperionifInNUcastPkts
amperionifInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

amperionifInDiscards.name: amperionifInDiscards
amperionifInDiscards.description: The number of inbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

amperionifInErrors.name: amperionifInErrors
amperionifInErrors.description: The number of inbound packets that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher-layer protocol.

amperionifInUnknownProtos.name: amperionifInUnknownProtos
amperionifInUnknownProtos.description: The number of packets received via the interface which were discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

amperionifOutOctets.name: amperionifOutOctets
amperionifOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

amperionifOutUcastPkts.name: amperionifOutUcastPkts
amperionifOutUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

amperionifOutNUcastPkts.name: amperionifOutNUcastPkts
amperionifOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address, including those that were discarded or not sent.

amperionifOutDiscards.name: amperionifOutDiscards
amperionifOutDiscards.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

amperionifOutErrors.name: amperionifOutErrors
amperionifOutErrors.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

amperionifOutQLen.name: amperionifOutQLen
amperionifOutQLen.description: The length of the output packet queue (in packets).

amperionifSpecific.name: amperionifSpecific
amperionifSpecific.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular media being used to realize the interface. For example, if the interface is realized by an ethernet, then the value of this object refers to a document defining objects specific to ethernet. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntatically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

amperionWirelessConfigKey.name: amperionWirelessConfigKey
amperionWirelessConfigKey.description: 802.11 encryption or scrambling keys and encryption mode.

amperionWirelessLinkQuality.name: amperionWirelessLinkQuality
amperionWirelessLinkQuality.description: A measure of how good the received signal is.

amperionWirelessSignalLevel.name: amperionWirelessSignalLevel
amperionWirelessSignalLevel.description: Received signal strength (how strong the received signal is).

amperionWirelessNoiseLevel.name: amperionWirelessNoiseLevel
amperionWirelessNoiseLevel.description: Background noise level (when no packet is transmited).

amperionWirelessActivate.name: amperionWirelessActivate
amperionWirelessActivate.description: Command to activate 802.11 parameters on demand.

amperionWirelessConfigBitRate.name: amperionWirelessConfigBitRate
amperionWirelessConfigBitRate.description: The bit transmission rate in Megabits per second. (0 = autonegotiated)

amperionWirelessConfigWDSPeer.name: amperionWirelessConfigWDSPeer
amperionWirelessConfigWDSPeer.description: The MAC address of any WDS peer.

ampMacAcceptTable.name: ampMacAcceptTable
ampMacAcceptTable.description: List of Mac address to be accepted

macAcceptTableWirelessIf.name: macAcceptTableWirelessIf
macAcceptTableWirelessIf.description: The wireless interface (e.g. wlan0) that ACL table is applied to.

accessControlStatus.name: accessControlStatus
accessControlStatus.description: Status of the access control table

amperionipAddrTable.name: amperionipAddrTable
amperionipAddrTable.description: The table of addressing information relevant to this entity's IP addresses.

amperionipAdEntAddr.name: amperionipAdEntAddr
amperionipAdEntAddr.description: The IP address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

amperionipAdEntIfName.name: amperionipAdEntIfName
amperionipAdEntIfName.description: The name which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

amperionipAdEntNetMask.name: amperionipAdEntNetMask
amperionipAdEntNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

amperionipAdEntBcastAddr.name: amperionipAdEntBcastAddr
amperionipAdEntBcastAddr.description: The value of the least-significant bit in the IP broadcast address used for sending datagrams on the (logical) interface associated with the IP address of this entry. For example, when the Internet standard all-ones broadcast address is used, the value will be 1. This value applies to both the subnet and network broadcasts addresses used by the entity on this (logical) interface.

amperionipAdEntReasmMaxSize.name: amperionipAdEntReasmMaxSize
amperionipAdEntReasmMaxSize.description: The size of the largest IP datagram which this entity can re-assemble from incoming IP fragmented datagrams received on this interface.

amperionipAdEntActivate.name: amperionipAdEntActivate
amperionipAdEntActivate.description: Command to activate the new IP address/netmask on demand.

rowStatus.name: rowStatus
rowStatus.description: A special field used to create new rows.

upstreamDownstreamRatio.name: upstreamDownstreamRatio
upstreamDownstreamRatio.description: Upstream bandwidth to downstream bandwidth ratio

qosStatus.name: qosStatus
qosStatus.description: Enable or disable status of Qos

ipRouteDest.name: ipRouteDest
ipRouteDest.description: The destination IP address of this route. An entry with a value of 0.0.0.0 is considered a default route. Multiple routes to a single destination can appear in the table, but access to such multiple entries is dependent on the table- access mechanisms defined by the network management protocol in use.

ipRouteIfIndex.name: ipRouteIfIndex
ipRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

ipRouteMetric1.name: ipRouteMetric1
ipRouteMetric1.description: The primary routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

ipRouteMetric2.name: ipRouteMetric2
ipRouteMetric2.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

ipRouteMetric3.name: ipRouteMetric3
ipRouteMetric3.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

ipRouteMetric4.name: ipRouteMetric4
ipRouteMetric4.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

ipRouteNextHop.name: ipRouteNextHop
ipRouteNextHop.description: The IP address of the next hop of this route. (In the case of a route bound to an interface which is realized via a broadcast media, the value of this field is the agent's IP address on that interface.)

ipRouteType.name: ipRouteType
ipRouteType.description: The type of route. Note that the values direct(3) and indirect(4) refer to the notion of direct and indirect routing in the IP architecture. Setting this object to the value invalid(2) has the effect of invalidating the corresponding entry in the ipRouteTable object. That is, it effectively dissasociates the destination identified with said entry from the route identified with said entry. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ipRouteType object.

ipRouteProto.name: ipRouteProto
ipRouteProto.description: The routing mechanism via which this route was learned. Inclusion of values for gateway routing protocols is not intended to imply that hosts should support those protocols.

ipRouteAge.name: ipRouteAge
ipRouteAge.description: The number of seconds since this route was last updated or otherwise determined to be correct. Note that no semantics of `too old' can be implied except through knowledge of the routing protocol by which the route was learned.

ipRouteMask.name: ipRouteMask
ipRouteMask.description: Indicate the mask to be logical-ANDed with the destination address before being compared to the value in the ipRouteDest field. For those systems that do not support arbitrary subnet masks, an agent constructs the value of the ipRouteMask by determining whether the value of the correspondent ipRouteDest field belong to a class-A, B, or C network, and then using one of: mask network 255.0.0.0 class-A 255.255.0.0 class-B 255.255.255.0 class-C If the value of the ipRouteDest is 0.0.0.0 (a default route), then the mask value is also 0.0.0.0. It should be noted that all IP routing subsystems implicitly use this mechanism.

ipRouteMetric5.name: ipRouteMetric5
ipRouteMetric5.description: An alternate routing metric for this route. The semantics of this metric are determined by the routing-protocol specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this metric is not used, its value should be set to -1.

ipRouteInfo.name: ipRouteInfo
ipRouteInfo.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular routing protocol which is responsible for this route, as determined by the value specified in the route's ipRouteProto value. If this information is not present, its value should be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntatically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

ipDefRouteActivate.name: ipDefRouteActivate
ipDefRouteActivate.description: Command to activate the new default route.

optimizationTable.name: optimizationTable
optimizationTable.description: If Injector - This table contains the frequencies(channels) / gains / throughput of all the extractors down stream. If Extractor - This table should contain frequencies(channels) / gains / throughput for the the plc segment between this extractor and the injector/repeator upstream.

upStreamDownStream.name: upStreamDownStream
upStreamDownStream.description: This to indicate if this entry pertains to the upstream segment or the downstream segment

gpsInfo.name: gpsInfo
gpsInfo.description: GPS co-ordinates. Currently this is a string which means the machine just picks up whatever GPS info is defined in it's system group and sends it to the extractor

plcEventDescription.name: plcEventDescription
plcEventDescription.description: String to be sent in the plc up/down event. Will contain ip address of the unit which just went down or will say 'local system' if current system

tempFanState.name: tempFanState
tempFanState.description: The fans may be on or off.

tempFanTargetTemp.name: tempFanTargetTemp
tempFanTargetTemp.description: The target temperature is the average temperature we would like the system to operate at if possible. It is used to calculate how long the fans should stay on during a cycle which is part of a duty cycle algorithm. Temperature is in degrees celsius.

tempEventDescription.name: tempEventDescription
tempEventDescription.description: String to be sent with the temperature trap events.

tempHighWarnLimitTrap.name: tempHighWarnLimitTrap
tempHighWarnLimitTrap.description: The system temperature has exceeded the High Warning threshold.

tempHighErrorLimitTrap.name: tempHighErrorLimitTrap
tempHighErrorLimitTrap.description: The system temperature has exceeded the High Error Threshold.

tempLowWarnLimitTrap.name: tempLowWarnLimitTrap
tempLowWarnLimitTrap.description: The system temperature has gone below the Low Warning Threshold.

tempLowErrorLimitTrap.name: tempLowErrorLimitTrap
tempLowErrorLimitTrap.description: The system temperature has gone below the Low Error Threshold.

tempHighWarnLimit.name: tempHighWarnLimit
tempHighWarnLimit.description: The system temperature has exceeded a high temperature warning threshold. Temperature is in degrees Celsius.

tempHighErrorLimit.name: tempHighErrorLimit
tempHighErrorLimit.description: The system temperature has exceeded a high temperature error threshold. Temperature is in degrees Celsius.

tempLowWarnLimit.name: tempLowWarnLimit
tempLowWarnLimit.description: The system temperature has gone below a low temperature warning threshold. Temperature is in degrees Celscius.

tempLowErrorLimit.name: tempLowErrorLimit
tempLowErrorLimit.description: The system temperature has gone below the Low Temperature Error Threshold. The temperature is in degrees Celscius.

tempHighWarnHist.name: tempHighWarnHist
tempHighWarnHist.description: Hysteresis value for the High Temperature Warning Condition. Once the system temperature has reached or exceeded the High Temperature Warning threshold, it must go down to or below the Hysteresis temperature before sending the trap again. The hysteresis temperature is in degrees Celcius.
